    stem: "A 42-year-old woman presents with ascending weakness beginning in both feet 12 days after a gastrointestinal illness. She now has difficulty climbing stairs and her arms feel weak. Examination reveals symmetric proximal and distal weakness in all four limbs, areflexia, and mild distal sensory loss. She has no bladder or bowel dysfunction. Nerve conduction studies show prolonged F-waves and reduced motor nerve conduction velocities. CSF analysis reveals protein of 3.2 g/L with white cell count of 3 cells/µL. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
