    topic: "Neurology",
    subtopic: "Acute Stroke Management and Carotid Stenosis",
    stem: `A 71-year-old man is brought to the Emergency Department with right-sided weakness of his arm and leg. His past medical history is significant for myocardial infarction 3 years ago for which he takes aspirin 100 mg daily. Non-contrast brain CT scan excludes intracranial hemorrhage. Doppler ultrasonography shows bilateral carotid artery stenosis of 50%. Which one of the following would be the most appropriate initial management?`,
