    subtopic: "Migraine with aura",
    stem: `A 26-year-old woman presents with a history of recurrent visual problems. She describes that she frequently experiences glimmering flashes in her vision for about 10 to 15 minutes each time, which are entirely resolved every time. She also has experienced global headaches, which worsen with exertion. Visual acuity, visual fields, eye movements and pupillary reflexes are normal on examination. The fundoscopic examination is inconclusive. There are no focal neurological deficits on central nervous system examination either. Which one of the following could be the most likely diagnosis?`,
