    topic: "Neurology",
    subtopic: "Goodpasture syndrome (anti-GBM disease)",
    stem: `A 22-year-old man presents to the emergency department with cough and dyspnea of one-week duration, as well as fatigue, decreased urine output and dark-coloured urine. Physical examination is otherwise inconclusive. Which one of the following is the single most accurate investigation to establish a diagnosis?`,
