    subtopic: "Urge incontinence - detrusor instability",
    stem: `A 69-year-old man presents to your GP clinic with a complaint of urinary incontinence. He explains that he cannot make it to the bathroom once he feels the urge to pass urine. He denies any dysuria. Which one of the following could be the most likely underlying cause of this presentation?`,
