    topic: "Neurology",
    subtopic: "Gross hematuria - renal mass evaluation",
    stem: `A 50-year-old man presents with complaints of several episodes of painless gross hematuria and a mass he felt in his left loin recently. The significant finding on examination is a non-tender loin mass. Urine analysis shows blood in the urine. Urine culture is negative. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
