    explanation: `This patient presents with acute urinary retention secondary to benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH). After catheterization for immediate relief, the next appropriate step is to assess renal function by measuring serum creatinine. Urinary retention can lead to post-renal acute kidney injury (AKI) due to increased back-pressure on the kidneys. Measuring serum creatinine helps determine if there has been any renal impairment as a result of the retention. This is a critical assessment before considering further management options. PSA level (option A) may be considered but is not the immediate priority after catheterization. A bladder scan (option B) is useful for assessing post-void residual but is not the next priority. An abdominal CT scan (option C) is not indicated at this stage. Urine cytology (option E) is not appropriate in this acute presentation.`,
