    stem: `A 47-year-old man presents to your practice with scrotal swelling. The swelling is not painful and has been there for the past four months. He does not feel bothered by the swelling and has just come to see you because his wife has forced him to. On examination, there is a non-tender swelling in the left testis. Ultrasonography shows the mass to be a cyst within the right testis. Which one of the following would be the next best step in management?`,
