    subtopic: "Testicular Cancer Diagnosis",
    stem: `A 25-year-old man presents with a painless right scrotal lump that he noticed while taking a shower three days ago. There is no tenderness or other abnormal findings, except asymptomatic enlargement of the right testis. The epididymis and spermatic cord can be felt in their normal positions. An ultrasound scan is performed, which is shown in the accompanying photograph. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
